word_mean_info__list.difference: 侧重指战争中的一次较全面、时间较长的战斗，也指陆军或海军在某一特定地区进行的战斗，或个人之间的争斗。
最普通用词，含义广，指战斗、斗争或打斗。
指激烈或时间持续长的战斗或奋力斗争。
泛指军事行动，尤指小规模的战斗，甚至是格斗。
通常指在一场大的战争中在某一地区进行的一连串有既定目的的军事行动。也可作引申用。
侧重指战争状态或具体的作战方法。
是战争的总称，一般指包括多个战役的大规模战争。

bilingual.source: She had to struggle to make ends meet.
bilingual.target: 她不得不奋斗才能维持生计。

bilingual.source: They untiringly struggle for a better life.
bilingual.target: 他们为了更好的生活不懈奋斗。
我们必须不懈奋斗，才能取得成功。

bilingual.source: He continues to struggle to achieve his dreams.
bilingual.target: 他为了实现梦想而不断奋斗。

bilingual.source: His spirit of struggle has inspired many people.
bilingual.target: 他的奋斗精神激励了很多人。

bilingual.source: The struggle for nationhood united the people.
bilingual.target: 为了国家地位而奋斗团结了人民。

bilingual.source: The story of the orphan's struggle was deeply touching.
bilingual.target: 孤儿奋斗的故事非常感人。

bilingual.source: There are always many moments of struggle in life.
bilingual.target: 生活中总会有许多奋斗的时刻。

bilingual.source: He will struggle to achieve his dreams no matter what.
bilingual.target: 无论如何，他都会奋斗实现他的梦想。

bilingual.source: We must struggle together to overcome these difficulties.
bilingual.target: 我们必须一起奋斗，才能克服这些困难。

list.abstract: struggle（英 [ˈstrʌɡl]，美 [ˈstrʌɡl]），英语单词，作动词用，为斗争；抵抗；挣扎。作名词用，为斗争；抵抗；奋斗。短语搭配有struggle with（与…斗争），例句为“Just another round of struggle for beauty.（只是又一轮对美的争夺。）” struggle形容词类近义词有apply oneselfl，名词类近义词有effort、competition、pain等，名词形式为struggler，形容词形式为struggling。

yingyinNormal.en: But for too many families across the country paying for higher education is a constant struggle.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但对于全国众多的家庭而言，支付大学的学费却是长期的奋斗。

yingyinNormal.en: After all that effort most of the students still struggle to speak comfortably with natives and don't have perfect pronunciation.
yingyinNormal.zh: 经过那么多努力，许多学生还是在和英语奋斗，无法自信地和外国人对话，也没有完美发音。

yingyinNormal.en: My only hope for you is that you have the courage to struggle and evolve well to make your life as great as it can be. Thank you, and goodbye.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我只希望你有勇气去奋斗，去发展，而想与身边出色的人一起能让你的生活精彩纷呈。谢谢你再会。

yingyinNormal.en: War is a struggle. Struggle breeds greatness.
yingyinNormal.zh: 战争就是抗争，抗争孕育伟大。

yingyinNormal.en: Spotted on the steps of the met, and S. and B. power struggle.
yingyinNormal.zh: 发现在大都会美术馆的阶梯上S和B针锋相对。

yingyinNormal.en: What do you think? You think I'm going to struggle with anything?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你觉得呢？你觉得我会怕什么吗？
yingyinNormal.videoNameZh: 《大卫·贝克汉姆：探索未知之境》

yingyinNormal.en: I realized that if I fail to do that, I will be a failure. I struggle with this now.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果我做不到这一点我将是一个失败。这就是我现在的挣扎。

yingyinNormal.en: Why should I struggle to be popular when I can be these people's empress fairy queen?
yingyinNormal.zh: 当我可以成为这些人的女王，我又何苦再费尽心思变得受欢迎呢？

yingyinNormal.en: Sunlight is often unable to pierce the glue. Even plants struggle to photosynthesis on the worst days.
yingyinNormal.zh: 黑霾压城，阳光往往无法穿透。在最糟糕的时候，即使植物也只能勉强进行光合作用。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, it certainly would be easier. You have no idea what it's like to struggle with recognizing emotional cues.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这至少会让相处简单很多啊。你们压根就不会懂读不懂别人情绪的复杂心情。

yingyinNormal.en: I don't want those memories erased by the struggle to fit behind a table, the taxi drivers who refuse to take me.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我不想让那些记忆被抹去，要坐着轮椅挤到桌边，还有那些拒载我的出租车司机们。

yingyinNormal.en: Each type of flower that you see is using color in a struggle to get noticed by insects. And there isn't much time.
yingyinNormal.zh: 大家看到的各种花都是在用自身的颜色，去争奇斗艳 以吸引昆虫的注意，时间非常紧迫。

yingyinNormal.en: The muscles in my wrist are cramping as I struggle to finish this sentence. Ow, ow, oh, the pain. Love, Sheldon. Fine. And Amy.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我忍着用肌肉在抽筋的手腕艰苦地写完这句子。哎哟，哎哟，疼死我了。爱你的谢尔顿敬上。行行行。"谢尔顿与艾米敬上"。

yingyinNormal.en: Science shows that when you struggle to solve a problem or make a new argument, you're actually forming new connections in your brain.
yingyinNormal.zh: 科学研究表明，当你经过千辛万苦解决了一个问题或提出一个新的观点时，你的大脑细胞就多了一条连接。

yingyinNormal.en: Sir, I appreciate the struggle you have been through, and I am very sorry to have caused you pain. Believe me, it was unconsciously done.
yingyinNormal.zh: 先生，我感激你的挣扎，但我非常遗憾，给你的只有痛苦，这个决定是潜意思下的。

yingyinNormal.en: We all struggle with different things at different times, until we either choose to give up, or until we die and become part of the larger evolutionary story.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不同时间中我们为不同的事挣扎，直到我们选择放弃或是死去，并变成更大的演化故事中的一部分。

yingyinNormal.en: And as poor as my family was, we still were a lot better off than a lot of your families, who not only had to struggle through poverty but had to fight racism as well.
yingyinNormal.zh: 虽然我家挺穷的，但还是比在座的许多家庭宽裕不少，你们不仅要和贫穷斗争，还得和种族歧视斗争。

yingyinNormal.en: The things we are striving for are just the bait. Struggling to get them forces us to evolve, and it is this struggle toward personal evolution with others that is the reward.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们追求的事情只是诱饵。实现目标的挣扎迫使我们不断发展，正是这些挣扎促进了个人发展，这就是回报。

yingyinNormal.en: You know what truth is? The struggle could use some more muscle. Aye look, I'll tell you what, we will bust you both out of here, but understand this, from now on you work for me.
yingyinNormal.zh: 其实我们在这场战争中的确需要同伴。这样吧，我们将你俩都弄出来，但是你们俩得明白，从现在起你们为我卖命。

yingyinNormal.en: Ms. What was our struggle for? And not just any "Ms. Pac-man," but an original 1982 fully reconditioned podium-style unit, with original coin return. They're even throwing in the stool.
yingyinNormal.zh: 是女士，刚刚纠正你多久了？不是普通的“吃豆女士游戏机”而是1982年原装修复的矮款，带有原始的退币口，他们还送了凳子呢。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

derivative_info_list.mean: adj. 努力的；奋斗的；苦斗的

word_family.mean: v. 斗争；抵抗；挣扎；奋斗；努力；争斗；冲突；挣扎求生；疲于应付；艰难行进

word_level_phrase_info.brief_definition: 进行斗争；和...作斗争；对抗

sense_info_list.en: to try very hard to do something when it is difficult or when there are a lot of problems

examination_example.sentence: A long <highlight>struggle</highlight> will be needed to avoid a future of digital feudalism.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 要避免未来出现数字封建主义，我们需要进行长期的奋斗。

examination_example.sentence: Schneider, a 27-year-old auto technician from the Chicago suburbs, says he <highlight>struggled</highlight> to find a job after graduating from college.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 来自芝加哥郊区的27岁汽车技师施耐德说，他大学毕业后找工作很艰难。

examination_example.sentence: When you are <highlight>struggling</highlight> to achieve something important you should believe in yourself and be sure that your decision is the best.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当你努力完成一些重要的事情时，你应该相信自己，并确信你的决定是最好的。

sense_info_list.en: to fight against someone or something in order to prevent a bad situation or result
sense_info_list.zh: 抗争; 斗争; 挣扎

examination_example.sentence: A few wealthy people will own all the capital, and the masses will <highlight>struggle</highlight> in an impoverished wasteland.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 少数富人将拥有全部资本，而群众将在贫困的荒地中挣扎。

examination_example.sentence: The court's ruling is a step forward in the <highlight>struggle</highlight> against both corruption and official favoritism.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 法院的裁决使与腐败和徇私舞弊的斗争向前迈进一步。

examination_example.sentence: "The history of all hitherto existing society is the history of class <highlight>struggles</highlight>," wrote Marx and Engels in The Communist Manifesto.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 马克思和恩格斯在《共产党宣言》中写道：“迄今为止，所有现存社会的历史都是阶级斗争的历史。”

sense_info_list.en: to compete or argue with someone, especially in order to get something
a forceful or violent effort to get free of restraint or resist attack
sense_info_list.zh: 搏斗; 扭打; 挣扎

word_usage.usage:
struggle against sth.和struggle with sb./sth.这两者都有“反抗”的意思，区别在于：
struggle against多指在艰难环境下奋起反抗或斗争。
struggle with则指试图控制某人或克服某物。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>

sense_info_list.en:
a determined effort under difficulties;
try very hard to do something when it is difficult or when there are a lot of problems
sense_info_list.zh: 努力争取/争夺; 奋斗

examination_example.sentence: Many of us who aren't mathematicians at heart (or engineers by trade) may <highlight>struggle</highlight> to remember the last time we used calculus (微积分).
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们当中的许多人如果不是数学家(或职业是工程师)可能很难记得上一次使用微积分是什么时候。

examination_example.sentence: Surfing the Internet during class doesn't just steal focus from the educator; it also hurts students who're already <highlight>struggling</highlight> to grasp the material.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在课堂上网上冲浪不仅会窃取教育者的注意力; 它还伤害了那些已经在努力掌握学习材料的学生。

examination_example.sentence: Until students are able to resists the pull of social networking, testing, and endlessly surfing the web, they may continue to <highlight>struggle</highlight> in their classes.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 除非学生们能够抵制社交网络、考试和无休止的上网，否则他们可能会在课堂上继续挣扎。

examination_example.sentence: To begin to figure out how computers are <highlight>struggling</highlight>, researchers tested a variety of facial-recognition algorithms (算法) as they scaled up in complexity.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 为了了解计算机的问题何在，研究人员不断增加其复杂性以测试一系列的面部识别算法。

examination_example.sentence: Meanwhile, Macy's has simply <highlight>struggled</highlight> to lure consumers who are more interested in spending on travel or dining out than on new clothes or accessories.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 同时，梅西百货在努力吸引那些对旅行或外出就餐而不是购买新衣服或配饰感兴趣的消费者。

sense_info_list.en:
a forceful or violent effort to get free of restraint or resist attack;
to fight against someone or something in order to prevent a bad situation or result

examination_example.sentence: Nowadays celebrities steal lyrics from each other and <highlight>struggle</highlight> with copyright violation accusations or straightforwardly claim themselves to be the authors.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如今，名人互相窃取歌词，并与侵犯版权的指控作斗争，或者直接声称自己是作者。

a determined effort under difficulties; 
try very hard to do something when it is difficult or when there are a lot of problems
sense_info_list.zh: 努力争取/争夺; 奋斗

examination_example.sentence: Without numbers, healthy human adults <highlight>struggle</highlight> to precisely distinguish and recall quantities as low as four.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 没有数字，健康的成年人很难精确区分和回忆低至4的数量。

examination_example.sentence: A reasonable assumption—don't families <highlight>struggle</highlight> to avoid nursing homes and suffer real guilt if they can't?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一个合理的假设——难道家庭不是在努力避免疗养院吗？如果无法避免，难道不是会遭受真正的负罪感吗？

examination_example.sentence: That's the real <highlight>struggle</highlight> because right now I do live in Holland but I really don't socialize much with Dutch people.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 那是十足的难事，因为现在我确实住在荷兰，但我不怎么和荷兰人交往。

sense_info_list.en:
a forceful or violent effort to get free of restraint or resist attack; 
to fight against someone or something in order to prevent a bad situation or result

examination_example.sentence: We would all <highlight>struggle</highlight> with even basic quantitative distinctions.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 即使是基本的数量差异，我们都会很纠结。

examination_example.sentence: Yet numberless people <highlight>struggle</highlight> with tasks that require precise discrimination between quantities.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 然而，无数人在与需要精确区分数量的任务作斗争。

examination_example.sentence: A research group has found that Americans who are <highlight>struggling</highlight> are thought to be lazy and to have made the wrong decisions.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一个研究小组发现，正在奋斗的美国人被认为是懒惰的，做出了错误的决定。

sense_info_list.en: a determined effort under difficulties; try very hard to do something when it is difficult or when there are a lot of problems

examination_example.sentence: After <highlight>struggling</highlight> for quite a while, I made a difficult decision—leaving my job and studying my design course full time.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在苦苦挣扎了一段时间后，我做出了一个艰难的决定：离开工作，全天学习设计课程。

examination_example.sentence: This was the first time I <highlight>struggled</highlight> to learn a song.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这是我第一次努力学一首歌。

examination_example.sentence: Having your grandchildren far away is hard, especially knowing your adult child is <highlight>struggling</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 让你的孙辈远离家乡是很困难的，尤其是知道你的成年子女正在奋斗。

sense_info_list.en: a forceful or violent effort to get free of restraint or resist attack; to fight against someone or something in order to prevent a bad situation or result

examination_example.sentence: Pruitt tries to give his donations to families that are truly <highlight>struggling</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 普鲁特试图把他的捐款捐给真正贫困的家庭。

examination_example.sentence: We've all been there: surrounded by people who are deeply focused on their smartphones or, worse, <highlight>struggling</highlight> with the uncomfortable silence.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们都有过这样的经历：周围的人全神贯注地盯着自己的智能手机，或者更糟的是，在令人不安的沉默中挣扎。

sense_info_list.en: a determined effort under difficulties; try very hard to do something when it is difficult or when there are a lot of problems

examination_example.sentence: While many teenagers are <highlight>struggling</highlight> (奋斗) to write articles for their exams, Jin Minzhe has already written a whole book.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当许多青少年还在努力为考试写文章时，金敏哲已经写了一整本书。

examination_example.sentence: I appreciate someone who knows when it is time to let kids <highlight>struggle</highlight> a little.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我很感激那些知道什么时候该让孩子们努力一点的人。

examination_example.sentence: Are you <highlight>struggling</highlight> to consider what to do for your mom on Mother’s Day?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你是否正纠结于在母亲节为你的妈妈做些什么?

sense_info_list.en: a forceful or violent effort to get free of restraint or resist attack; to fight against someone or something in order to prevent a bad situation or result

examination_example.sentence: Several modern writers saw the process of education as a <highlight>struggle</highlight> (斗争) against human nature.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一些现代作家把教育的过程看作是与人性的斗争。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Struggling</highlight> (斗争) with this, he went into the forest alone.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 挣扎着说完，他独自走进了森林。

examination_example.sentence: "So you know, all the time you were <highlight>struggling</highlight>, you were actually growing strong roots.” the old man said.
examination_example.sentence_trans: “所以你知道，在你挣扎的所有时间里，你实际上是在茁壮成长。”老人说。

sense_info_list.en: to be in danger of failing or being defeated

examination_example.sentence: Meanwhile, Lily was <highlight>struggling</highlight> in the ballet class as well.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 与此同时，莉莉也在芭蕾课上苦苦挣扎。

examination_example.sentence: How did Evan help those <highlight>struggling</highlight> in Puerto Rico?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 埃文是如何帮助那些在波多黎各挣扎的人？

examination_example.sentence: “I’ve been seeing, all over the news, people <highlight>struggling</highlight>.” Evan said.
examination_example.sentence_trans: “我一直在新闻上看到，人们在挣扎。”埃文说。
